emuInput.TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom Bailey W. Williams and bride Jayne Lewis Woodson Williams, cutting two tiered wedding cake in dining room of Hijar Manor, home of Mr. and Mrs. Ira Lewis
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1952, pg. 10 reads: "Mr. and Mrs. Bailey W. Williams...on New York honeymoon." Portion of article reads: "Woodson-Williams Rites Are Social Highlight - Pittsburgh- In a most charming home wedding, held at the celebrated Hijar Manor, above the city and overlooking the far reaches of Wilkinsburg, Mrs. Jayne Lewis Woodson, daughter of Mrs. Harriette Lewis and the late Ira F. Lewis, became the bride of Bailey W. Williams, son of Mrs. Margaret Williams...The marriage was an event of Saturday morning, Nov. 23, at 11:30, with the Rev. Charles H. Foggie officiating."
